{"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I need to create the core new-thread flow function. This will be a module-level function (like `continue_thread` and `load_threads_for_issue` in `main.rs`). Let me add it to `main.rs`. First, let me also add a helper to snapshot thread IDs. Let me add a function to `amp/thread.rs`:"},{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_vrtx_01UhmqxLd1nU97HdGaHYHqoe","name":"edit_file","input":{"path":"/Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/amp/thread.rs","old_str":"/// List all thread summaries from the default Amp threads directory.\n///\n/// Scans `~/.local/share/amp/threads/*.json` and parses metadata from each file.\n/// Threads that fail to parse are silently skipped.\npub fn list_threads() -> Result<Vec<ThreadSummary>> {","new_str":"/// Snapshot all thread IDs from a given directory by listing `*.json` filenames.\n///\n/// Returns a set of thread IDs (filenames without `.json` extension).\npub fn snapshot_thread_ids(dir: &Path) -> std::collections::HashSet<String> {\n    let mut ids = std::collections::HashSet::new();\n    if let Ok(entries) = std::fs::read_dir(dir) {\n        for entry in entries.flatten() {\n            let path = entry.path();\n            if path.extension().is_some_and(|ext| ext == \"json\") {\n                if let Some(stem) = path.file_stem().and_then(|s| s.to_str()) {\n                    ids.insert(stem.to_string());\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    ids\n}\n\n/// List all thread summaries from the default Amp threads directory.\n///\n/// Scans `~/.local/share/amp/threads/*.json` and parses metadata from each file.\n/// Threads that fail to parse are silently skipped.\npub fn list_threads() -> Result<Vec<ThreadSummary>> {"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":640,"cache_read_input_tokens":82402,"output_tokens":543,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff6b-1020-7104-aaed-de58f4c44518"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01UhmqxLd1nU97HdGaHYHqoe","content":"{\"diff\":\"```diff\\nIndex: /Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/amp/thread.rs\\n===================================================================\\n--- /Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/amp/thread.rs\\toriginal\\n+++ /Users/jmawson/Development/sourcery/ishi/src/amp/thread.rs\\tmodified\\n@@ -165,8 +165,26 @@\\n     let path = threads_dir.join(format!(\\\"{}.json\\\", id));\\n     read_thread_summary(&path)\\n }\\n \\n+/// Snapshot all thread IDs from a given directory by listing `*.json` filenames.\\n+///\\n+/// Returns a set of thread IDs (filenames without `.json` extension).\\n+pub fn snapshot_thread_ids(dir: &Path) -> std::collections::HashSet<String> {\\n+    let mut ids = std::collections::HashSet::new();\\n+    if let Ok(entries) = std::fs::read_dir(dir) {\\n+        for entry in entries.flatten() {\\n+            let path = entry.path();\\n+            if path.extension().is_some_and(|ext| ext == \\\"json\\\") {\\n+                if let Some(stem) = path.file_stem().and_then(|s| s.to_str()) {\\n+                    ids.insert(stem.to_string());\\n+                }\\n+            }\\n+        }\\n+    }\\n+    ids\\n+}\\n+\\n /// List all thread summaries from the default Amp threads directory.\\n ///\\n /// Scans `~/.local/share/amp/threads/*.json` and parses metadata from each file.\\n /// Threads that fail to parse are silently skipped.\\n```\",\"lineRange\":[169,191]}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff6b-1020-7104-aaed-de58f4c44518"}
